    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">An </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">unbiased </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">estimate, or measurement, is one in which the expected value of the error (which can be positive or negative) is zero. &#160;By definition, measurements affected by </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">systematic error</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> are biased.</text></para>
